Package io.github.jornegitgud.galaxyquest

Class GalaxyRenderer

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.jornegitgud.galaxyquest.GalaxyRenderer
  • public class GalaxyRenderer
extends java.lang.Object
    The GalaxyRenderer takes Galaxy objects and translates them into a visible GUI for the user. The GalaxyRenderer is responsible for rendering sprites in the correct positions, with the correct sizes, in the correct order.

        public GalaxyRenderer​(javafx.stage.Stage stage,
                      GalaxySettings settings)
               throws java.io.IOException
        GalaxyRenderer's constructor takes a stage and a copy of the GalaxySettings in order to construct the scene (render window in correct size, setup background, etc)
        Parameters:
        stage - The stage to use for rendering galaxies onto.
        settings - The galaxy's settings, used to determine the width and height of the window.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - throws if a sprite could not be found.

      • addSprite

        public void addSprite​(Galaxy galaxy,
                      Tile tile,
                      java.lang.String spritePath)
        This method adds a static sprite on top of the galaxy scene. (i.e. flags on top of planets). The player is always rendered on top of static sprites.
        Parameters:
        galaxy - is the galaxy to add the sprite on
        tile - the tile to add the sprite on
        spritePath - is the string to the location of the sprite.
